The paper presents a prototype real-world environment for reinforcement learning in robotics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and the focus on benchmarking and research also suggest that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The navigation task involves using camera input, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the integration into an existing ecosystem and the mention of managing a physical robotics system suggest that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
